WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:03.600
Overlapping Triangles: Find the Shaded Area.

2
00:00:03.550 --> 00:00:08.450
The answer is hidden by default. so click Show Answer above to view the solution.

3
00:00:08.450 --> 00:00:09.450
Problem.

4
00:00:09.450 --> 00:00:15.762
Diagram: two congruent triangles overlap. and the shaded region in the middle is a trapezoid.

5
00:00:15.762 --> 00:00:22.637
Given: the two triangles are congruent. and the diagram shows lengths six and nine. with height six.

6
00:00:22.637 --> 00:00:25.125
Find the area of the shaded region.

7
00:00:25.125 --> 00:00:26.287
Main idea.

8
00:00:26.287 --> 00:00:32.450
Split the figure around the shaded trapezoid into three parts. labeled one. two. and three.

9
00:00:32.450 --> 00:00:36.600
Because the two triangles are congruent. their areas are equal.

10
00:00:36.600 --> 00:00:40.100
Part one plus part two equals part two plus part three.

11
00:00:40.100 --> 00:00:44.287
Subtract part two from both sides. and we get the next equation.

12
00:00:44.287 --> 00:00:46.450
Part one equals part three.

13
00:00:46.450 --> 00:00:50.787
So the shaded trapezoid can be computed directly as one trapezoid.

14
00:00:50.787 --> 00:00:52.075
Calculation.

15
00:00:52.075 --> 00:00:56.762
The trapezoid has top base six. bottom base nine. and height six.

16
00:00:56.762 --> 00:00:59.287
Use the trapezoid area formula.

17
00:00:59.287 --> 00:01:05.825
Area equals open parenthesis top base plus bottom base close parenthesis times height divided by two.

18
00:01:05.825 --> 00:01:11.850
Area equals open parenthesis six plus nine close parenthesis times six divided by two.

19
00:01:11.850 --> 00:01:17.162
Area equals fifteen times six divided by two. which equals forty-five.

20
00:01:17.162 --> 00:01:19.862
Shaded area equals forty-five.

21
00:01:19.862 --> 00:01:20.900
Summary.

22
00:01:20.900 --> 00:01:30.237
The key is not brute force: first use congruent triangles to get part one equals part three. then treat the shaded part as an ordinary trapezoid.

23
00:01:30.237 --> 00:01:32.600
Final answer: forty-five.

